What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take this class if you hope to find two or three topics within to which you will dedicate yourself in further private study. It is not a good "one and done" survey course.

I would absolutely recommend this class if you are interested in European and American history. In particular, I think the class does a great job of analyzing the changes in the way the United States has participated in the international system.
